00:47:35.900 --> 00:47:38.720
The first year, I didn't know
what to expect so I sort of

00:47:38.720 --> 00:47:42.610
had that moment of panic and
said OK, pull it together.

00:47:42.610 --> 00:47:47.556
This year I'm like well, you
know what's ahead of you.

00:47:47.556 --> 00:47:51.090
But do you have any tips or
advice for like that moment of

00:47:51.090 --> 00:47:55.670
jumping in and keeping
yourself together and

00:47:55.670 --> 00:48:00.075
completing what your goal is?

00:48:00.075 --> 00:48:01.365
LYNNE COX: I totally
understand that.

00:48:01.365 --> 00:48:04.050
I was just talking to a friend
of mine who played on the

00:48:04.050 --> 00:48:06.420
national team and who was an
amazing water polo player.

00:48:06.420 --> 00:48:10.200
And he said he did his first
triathlon with 1,200 people,

00:48:10.200 --> 00:48:11.680
maybe five years ago.

00:48:11.680 --> 00:48:14.750
And he said he had that moment
where 1,200 people were being

00:48:14.750 --> 00:48:15.890
released all at once.

00:48:15.890 --> 00:48:18.010
And he said, I was so anxious.

